    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-08-16T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-08-16T18:00:00-05:00" n="425"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d425">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">881.00/1261: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Diplomatic Agent and Consul General at Tangier</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Blake</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-08-16T19:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 16, 1926—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5. Referring to telegram No. 60 of August 15, 1 p.m., from the Ambassador in
                    Spain to the Department concerning Spanish control of the Tangier Zone.</p>
                <p>Please report by wire such cases as involve Spanish sphere of influence,
                    settlement of which should be required by this Government before recognizing the
                    Spanish protectorate in that area as it exists now.<note n="8" xml:id="d425fn8"
                        >For correspondence previously printed concerning the attitude of the United
                        States on the subject of the Spanish Zone in Morocco, see <ref
                            target="frus1917#pg_1095">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1917, pp. 1095</ref>–<ref
                            target="frus1917#pg_1096">1096</ref>; also <ref
                            target="frus1923v02#pg_585">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, 1923, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>,
                            pp. 585</ref>.</note> Also a brief statement of such further safeguards
                    as, in your judgment, should be prerequisites to recognition.</p>
                <p>It should not be divulged that Spain has approached this Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
